## Idea

Given a [[differentiable (âˆž,1)-category]] $\mathcal{C}$, then the [[(âˆž,1)-category]] of [[n-excisive functors]] from the [[pointed objects]] in $\mathcal{C}$ itself to $\mathcal{C}$ behaves like the [[bundles]] of order-$n$ [[Goodwillie calculus|Goodwillie derivatives]] over all [[objects]] of $\mathcal{C}$. Hence this is the analog of the $n$th order [[jet bundle]] in [[Goodwillie calculus]]. 

In particular for $n = 1$ this is the [[tangent (âˆž,1)-category]] of $\mathcal{C}$.

